{"abstract": "After criticism of its pay practices, the bank will make compensation partly dependent on the company\u2019s competitive performance.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2013/02/22/business/citi-changes-terms-of-executive-bonuses.html", "snippet": "After criticism of its pay practices, the bank will make compensation partly dependent on the company\u2019s competitive performance.", "lead_paragraph": "Responding to anger over executive pay, Citigroup is changing the way it calculates the bonuses given to top executives. It announced on Thursday that part of the $11.5 million in compensation awarded to the new chief executive, Michael L. Corbat, would be closely tied to performance.", "print_section": "B", "print_page": "1", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2013/02/22/business/Citi/Citi-jumbo.jpg", "height": 781, "width": 453, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2013/02/22/business/Citi/Citi-superJumbo.jpg", "height": 781, "width": 453, "subType": "superJumbo", "crop_name": "superJumbo", "legacy": {}}], "headline": {"main": "Citigroup Toughens Executive Bonus Rules", "kicker": null, "content_kicker": null, "print_headline": "Citigroup Toughens Executive Bonus Rules", "name": null, "seo": null, "sub": null}, "keywords": [{"name": "persons", "value": "Popper, Nathaniel", "rank": 1, "major": "N"}, {"name": "organizations", "value": "Citigroup Inc", "rank": 2, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Silver-Greenberg, Jessica", "rank": 3, "major": "N"}, {"name": "subject", "value": "Executive Compensation", "rank": 4, "major": "N"}, {"name": "subject", "value": "Banking and Financial Institutions", "rank": 5, "major": "N"}, {"name": "subject", "value": "Bonuses", "rank": 6, "major": "N"}], "pub_date": "2013-02-21T23:59:06+